WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.630 --> 00:00:04.420
Android wear notifications are the
easiest way to get started in the world

00:00:04.420 --> 00:00:05.520
of wearables.

00:00:05.520 --> 00:00:08.039
If you've got an Android
app with a notifications,

00:00:08.039 --> 00:00:10.250
they all ready work on the watch.

00:00:10.250 --> 00:00:13.290
If you've all ready enhanced
your notification with actions,

00:00:13.290 --> 00:00:15.590
such as next or previous.

00:00:15.590 --> 00:00:17.030
This is even better, and

00:00:17.030 --> 00:00:20.710
also automatically works with
no additional work required.

00:00:20.710 --> 00:00:24.240
You can take things further with Wear's
specific functionality that make

00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:27.800
your notifications even richer
experiences on the wrist.

00:00:27.800 --> 00:00:30.700
Stacks, which are like
inbox style notifications,

00:00:30.700 --> 00:00:34.080
now you can deliver multiple
items in a single bundle.

00:00:34.080 --> 00:00:38.080
Pages are for showing multiple screens
of information on the same topic.

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:40.020
But, remember to stay glanceable.

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:40.970
Replies.

00:00:40.970 --> 00:00:44.000
Now replies allow the user to
respond directly from the wearable

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:44.560
with their voice.

